Description. The holotype NTM C4203 is 4 cm high and 5 cm wide, the stalk is 2 cm high (
Fig. 1g
). The polyps are up to 1 mm wide and 0.45 mm high, and are grouped in long catkins.

NTM C4197 has different stalk sclerites than the holotype as its interior stalk spindles are longer and wider (
Fig. 19g
) and more capstans and derivatives of capstans are present in the surface layer of the base stalk ( Fig. 19 h-i). As the other characters are similar to the holotype I consider this to be infraspecific variation.
